this is a better way of creating a loop that doesn't affect threading 
```csharp
class Example
{
    void Example()
    {
        // setup a repeating call queue for hello every 250 milliseconds
        GetGame().GetCallQueue(CALL_CATEGORY_SYSTEM).CallLater(SayHello, 250, true);
    }

    void ~Example()
    {
        // remove repeating call queue when instance is destroyed
        GetGame().GetCallQueue(CALL_CATEGORY_SYSTEM).Remove(SayHello);
    }

    void SayHello()
    {
        Print("Hello World!"); // hello :)
    }
}
```

